description:
Job responsibilities:-

- Provide full range of secretarial and administrative support to Chairman;
- Manage calendars, meeting schedules, personal & family affairs including director's quarter maintenance, maids and drivers management, administrative support to the relatives of Chairman;
- Maintain filling system and confidential information in a professional manner;
- Closely liaise and coordinate with internal and external parties to ensure smooth business operations.

Jobs requirements:-

- Degree holder with 3 years solid experience;
- Excellent command in spoken and written English, Cantonese and Mandarin;
- Proficient PC knowledge in MS Word and Excel;
- Multi-tasking, well-organized, detail-minded with strong communication and interpersonal skills;
- Immediately available is highly preferred.

Responsibilities:


Provide full spectrum of secretarial and administrative support to Chairman in both business affairs and personal issues;
Organize the daily calendars and prepare meeting materials for internal and external meetings and appointments;
Coordinate with different departments and follow up on daily operation matters;
Serve as the primary point of contact for internal department and external parties on all matters pertaining to the Chairman;
Assist Chairman to handle emails & correspondences;
Deal with confidential matters with a high degree of professionalism and confidentiality;
Coordinate with drivers and helpers to ensure smooth operations;
Perform any other duties as assigned by the Chairman.

Requirements:


Bachelor Degree in Business Administration or related disciplines;
At least 8 years’ solid executive secretarial experience;
Logical thinking, presentable, hardworking, smart and well organized;
Proactive, fast-paced, self-motivated and able to work independently;
Proficient in PC applications, e.g. MS Office, Excel, PowerPoint and Chinese Word Processing is a MUST;
Immediate available is preferred.

We Offer:

Competitive remuneration package
5 Days Work & Bank Holidays
Attendance Bonus
Meal Allowance
Discretionary Bonus
Medical Insurance  

We provide attractive remuneration package and fringe benefits for the right candidate. Interested parties please send detailed resume with current and expected salaries to Human Resources Department by clicking "Apply Now" or fax to: 2530 2218.

All information collected will be used for recruitment purpose only, only shortlisted candidates will be notified.

Welcome to visit our website: http://www.bsgroup.com.hk/ for more information

Responsibilities:  

Office administration work such as general filing work and data input;
Manage office supplies and the smooth running of the department;
Organize meetings and conference calls;
Travel arrangement and travel expenses;
Provide day to day administrative support.

Requirement:  

Good communication, interpersonal and organization skills;
Self-initiative and detail-minded;
Proficient in MS Office and Chinese word processing;
Good command of spoken and written English and Chinese including Mandarin;
Able to provide service on 2 or 3 full days a week or half day from each day.
Immediately available is highly preferred.

We offer friendly working environment with competitive remuneration. If you are interested in joining our company, please click "Apply Now" to submit your application. 

ALL PERSONAL INFORMATION WE COLLECTED IS FOR THE PURPOSE OF RECRUITMENT ONLY

Please visit www.nuskin.com to find out more about us!

