DEPARTMENT OF ELECTRICAL ENGINEERING

Executive Assistant (Ref. 22011404-E)

Duties

The appointee will be required to:

(a) provide administrative support to both academic and research programmes;

(b) support a wide range of activities of the Unit, including administration of student-related matters (e.g. admission, registration, examination, timetabling and student record), and various student-related events and projects;

(c) provide secretarial support to meetings and committees;

(d) compile statistical reports and maintain database;

(e) support general office administration; and

(f) perform any other duties as assigned by the Head of the Unit or his delegates.
The appointee may be required to work outside office hours.

Qualifications

Applicants should have:

(a) a recognized degree or an equivalent qualification;

(b) at least two years of relevant post-qualification experience;

(c) a good command of both English and Chinese, with fluency in Putonghua being an advantage;

(d) proficiency in computer software applications including MS office (e.g. MS Excel, Word, PowerPoint) and Chinese word processing;

(e) good communication, interpersonal and time management skills; and

(f) self-motivation and the ability to work independently and proactively.

Preference will be given to those with experience in tertiary institutions/similar organizations.

Shortlisted candidates may be invited to sit for a written test and a computer test.

Remuneration and Conditions of Service

A highly competitive remuneration package will be offered. Initial appointment will be on a fixed-term one-year gratuity-bearing contract. Re-engagement thereafter is subject to mutual agreement. Applicants should state their current and expected salary in the application.

Application

Please send a completed application form by post to Human Resources Office, 13/F, Li Ka Shing Tower, The Hong Kong Polytechnic University, Hung Hom, Kowloon, Hong Kong or via email by clicking "Apply Now".  Application forms can be downloaded from https://www.polyu.edu.hk/hro/careers/guidelines_and_forms/forms.  If a separate curriculum vitae is to be provided, please still complete the application form which will help speed up the recruitment process.  Consideration of applications will commence on 26 January 2022 until the position is filled.  The University’s Personal Information Collection Statement for recruitment can be found at https://www.polyu.edu.hk/hro/careers/guidelines_and_forms/pics_for_recruitment.

PolyU is an equal opportunity employer committed to diversity and inclusivity.  All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to gender, ethnicity, nationality, family status or physical or mental disabilities.

Responsibilities:

Reporting to a Director
Provide full range of good quality secretarial and administrative support;
Manage all business and personal issues for the Director in professional manner, including but not limited to meeting and travel schedules, social events and functions co-ordination etc.;
Prepare business correspondences, presentation materials, compile reports and meeting minutes in a variety of formats independently and professionally;
Liaise with internal and external parties to ensure smooth business operations;
Manage payments, claims and reimbursements;
Handle sensitive and confidential data and documents in professional manner;
Assist in ad-hoc duties as assigned.


Requirements:           

University Graduate or equivalent;
Minimum 8 years’ relevant experience with proven track record in serving senior executives or directors, preferably in sizeable companies;
Ability of maintaining sensitive and confidential information with strictest confidence;
Proficient in MS Office applications with Chinese word processing;
Strong inter-personal and communication skills;
Excellent command of spoken and written English, Cantonese and Mandarin;
Mature, self-motivated, meticulous and able to handle multiple tasks with discretion.

This is a fixed-term contract position of minimum 2 years with possibility for renewal subject to organization need and individual performance. Responsibilities:
Providing all-rounded secretarial and administration service to the team including but not limited to managing daily appointments, calendar, travel itinerary and meetings; and preparing business correspondence;
Handling project documents and maintaining effective filing / database management systems;
Assisting in managing project documentation using project management software systems;
Handling enquiries and maintaining effective communication with internal and external customers; and
Assisting in ad hoc projects and assignments as required.

Requirements:

Diploma or above in Business Administration, Secretarial Studies or other related disciplines with at least 5 years' relevant working experience in project administration, work process management and/or document control; or Secondary level with at least 6 years' relevant working experience and formal secretarial training will also be considered
Good command of spoken and written English and Chinese. Knowledge of Putonghua is an advantage
Proficient in MS Office applications and project management software tools

FINANCE OFFICE

Senior Secretary (Ref. 22011230-IE)

Duties

The appointee will be required to:

(a) provide secretarial service to the Director of Finance and the Deputy Director of Finance, including arranging/coordinating departmental activities and committee meetings, maintaining calendar, scheduling appointments and making arrangements for off-campus meetings, travel and accommodation arrangements;

(b) provide administrative support to the day-to-day operation of the Finance Office, including recruitment and human resources matters, planning and arranging visits and events;

(c) manage meeting papers and materials of relevant University committees including compilation, distribution and record-keeping;

(d) handle information flow and maintain an effective record and filing system;

(e) handle sensitive and confidential matters in a professional manner;

(f) liaise with internal and external parties in a personable manner; and

(g) perform any other duties as assigned by the Director of Finance or her delegates.

Qualifications 

Applicants should:

(a) have a recognized degree plus at least three years of relevant post-qualification secretarial/administrative experience; 

(b) be able to communicate effectively in both written and spoken English and Chinese, with fluency in Putonghua being an advantage;

(c) have good computer literacy including Microsoft Word, Excel, PowerPoint and Chinese word processing;

(d) have good communication and interpersonal skills;

(e)  be well-organized and attentive to details; and

(f) be able to initiate appropriate actions, work independently and handle sensitive matters with alertness and care.

Shortlisted candidates will be invited to sit for a written test.

Remuneration and Conditions of Service

A highly competitive remuneration package will be offered.  Initial appointment will be on a fixed-term gratuity-bearing contract.  Re-engagement thereafter is subject to mutual agreement.  Applicants should state their current and expected salary in the application.




Application

Please send a completed application form by post to Human Resources Office, 13/F, Li Ka Shing Tower, The Hong Kong Polytechnic University, Hung Hom, Kowloon, Hong Kong or via email by clicking "Apply Now".  Application forms can be downloaded from https://www.polyu.edu.hk/hro/careers/guidelines_and_forms/forms.  If a separate curriculum vitae is to be provided, please still complete the application form which will help speed up the recruitment process. The closing date for application is Wednesday, 19 January 2022.  Applicants who are not invited to an interview within two months from the closing date should consider their applications unsuccessful. The University’s Personal Information Collection Statement for recruitment can be found at https://www.polyu.edu.hk/hro/careers/guidelines_and_forms/pics_for_recruitment.

PolyU is an equal opportunity employer committed to diversity and inclusivity.  All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to gender, ethnicity, nationality, family status or physical or mental disabilities.
